                <h1>What to Do If You’re Denied Employment Due to Background Check Errors</h1>
                <p>If you're refused employment due to background check errors, first request a copy of the report. Review it carefully for inaccuracies. Dispute any mistakes with the reporting agency and provide supporting evidence. Additionally, communicate with the employer to explain the discrepancies and demonstrate your qualifications for the position.</p>
